track_notes: Park near or around the forest road entrance SH683208, taking care not to block it. Follow the forest road NE for approx 400m. Take the track (not on 1:25K map) leading up and right (entrance and 1st 200m was badly damaged by forestry equipment in summer 2015). Follow this track up to gap in wall at SH691216. Pass to other side of wall and continue E on indistinct track to meet crossing main track 200m.  Turn left (N) and follow this track (also not on OS 1:25K) to gate in wall at SH693222. Over gate and head diagonally right up hill on obvious old track.  This zig zags up E until it heads N again.  It eventually ends abruptly at approx SH695226 on the edge of a marshy area. After this you have to find your own route making the best of the sheep tracks for the last 800 metres to the summit, firstly over Garn Fach, then a small descent, followed by a final climb through rocky bluffs to the summit.  Large cairn makes it obvious in bad weather. No walls or fences to climb, just one gate.

National Trust car park on A470 in Ganllwyd (£1 donation, in 2018). Information board shows 4 NT tracks. We will follow the red route onto the blue one. Cross road and river bridge to follow footpath into woods. Emerging to cross footbridge head straight for barn. Continue following the track, passing through a field gate and crossing the tramway at the ruin of a powder magazine. Now yellow markers appear, leading you through the spread of gold mine adits. Past the highest trial cut you will reach a gap in the boundary wall where it meets another wall, heading north west. Follow the wall, crossing a stile about half way up, until you reach a shoulder of Y Garn, where you turn left. Sheep tracks take you to the summit.
